Context

A government-aided autonomous college in Bidar, Karnataka wants to analyze student performance, attendance, demographics, fees, and extracurricular activities.
The dataset simulates multiple tables â€” each representing a domain like students, courses, attendance, etc.

These CSVs will serve as inputs for examples throughout all stages â€” from loading and cleaning (Stage 1) to joins, time, and categorical analysis (Stage 3).

ğŸ“ Dataset Structure (CSV Tables)
Table	File Name	Description	Key Columns
1	students.csv	Student demographic and academic master list	student_id
2	departments.csv	College departments metadata	dept_id
3	courses.csv	Courses offered, linked to departments	course_id, dept_id
4	enrollments.csv	Students registered per semester per course	enroll_id, student_id, course_id
5	attendance.csv	Daily or weekly attendance records per course	attendance_id, student_id, course_id, date
6	results.csv	Student semester-wise exam results	result_id, student_id, course_id, semester
7	fees.csv	Student fee payment details	receipt_id, student_id, payment_date
8	activities.csv	Student participation in extracurricular activities	activity_id, student_id
ğŸ§¾ 1. students.csv

Columns:

Column	Type	Description
student_id	int	Unique ID for each student
